Question: How do you believe ACME should better support organizations and cultural leaders?

Response ID: resp_2864
Response Text: There is only ONE answer to this problem that would be effective.  Get big finance COMPLETELY out of housing, and MOSTLY out of small commercial spaces. Completely, 100% full ban on corporate landlords, and out of state landlords with more than a couple properties. Complete ban on investment groups dealing in real estate and seize their assets.

It must be possible to make ends meet on a part time job, in housing with enough space to actually work on projects and store /support equipment, and must be possible to OWN a house for anyone working 40 hours a week. In addition, European style public transportation is an absolute non negotiable must.

Zoning requirements must be realigned to allow housing that would actually work for artists, like industrial and commercial spaces that would allow a few residents. And self built studios need support from a department that can help with code and expertise issues, with knowledge of these specialized needs. Apartments are completely unworkable for most artists and musicians. Live/work spaces should be the norm, not the exception.

And really, I wish we could ban 5 over 1s while we're at it, or at least require the commercial space to be full at all times 

A couple policies that would help would be exorbitant property tax for empty non primary residences and commercial spaces.  So that it would cost the property owner more to keep it empty than to let someone live/work there for free or sell it.

